<span style="font-family:'Century Gothic', sans-serif;font-size:14px;"><p><h2>How to update your email signature via Outlook accessed through a web browser</h2></p>
<p>Copy the email signature template below.</p>
<p>In Outlook web, navigate to <strong>Settings</strong> and select <strong>View all Outlook settings</strong>.</p>
<p>Click <strong>'Email'</strong> and then <strong>'Compose and reply'</strong>.</p>
<p>Select the text box and paste the email signature template.</p>
<p>Tick so the box is red for ‘Automatically include my signature on new messages I compose’. Tick so the box is red for ‘Automatically include my signature on messages I forward or reply to’.</p>
<p>Once the template is copied into Outlook, fill out your relevant contact details.</p>
<p>Select <strong>Save</strong> at the bottom of the page.</p>

